.TH "snd_pcm_stop_xrun" 9 "snd_pcm_stop_xrun" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_pcm_stop_xrun \- stop the running streams as XRUN
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_pcm_stop_xrun
.BI "(struct snd_pcm_substream *substream "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "substream" 12
the PCM substream instance
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This stops the given running substream (and all linked substreams) as XRUN.
Unlike \fBsnd_pcm_stop\fP, this function takes the substream lock by itself.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero if successful, or a negative error code.
